1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:07,339
Each partition has exactly one Leader replica and zero or more Follower replicas.

2
00:00:07,289 --> 00:00:12,355
The total number of replicas is the replication factor (RF).

3
00:00:12,355 --> 00:00:22,131
Followers continuously fetch from the leader using the same internal protocol as consumers, appending records to their local log.

4
00:00:22,131 --> 00:00:29,973
Here's something wild: Uber once had a major outage because their apache kafka system failed.

5
00:00:29,973 --> 00:00:32,197
Cost them millions.

